cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper deals with the problem of correcting group discriminations within a score function, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves probability density functions and linear programming, which are topics covered in cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper addresses the issue of minimizing discrimination, which is a topic in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
